39:47.995 --> 39:50.029
(LAUGHING): I wrote a whole book

39:50.030 --> 39:53.666
about how the farm saved me and
I completely meant it because,

39:53.667 --> 39:54.967
I don't know if you've heard,

39:54.968 --> 39:57.103
but, uh, I am nothing
if not fully committed.

39:57.104 --> 39:59.672
(CHUCKLES) I might've heard
something about that.

39:59.673 --> 40:01.040
Yeah, about those stories.

40:01.041 --> 40:03.576
They're all true.

40:03.577 --> 40:06.979
Well, they do keep
getting one part wrong.

40:06.980 --> 40:08.947
I didn't throw a chair.

40:09.949 --> 40:12.952
I threw a table...

40:12.953 --> 40:15.288
at a chair...

40:15.289 --> 40:17.890
of the Armed Services Committee.

40:17.891 --> 40:21.828
We had just been, uh, traveling
through Southeast Asia,

40:21.829 --> 40:23.930
setting up aid programs
when I found out this guy

40:23.931 --> 40:25.898
had let himself get bribed

40:25.899 --> 40:29.302
in the... the dumbest way imaginable

40:29.303 --> 40:32.338
and I just lost it.

40:32.339 --> 40:34.774
Do I regret it? Of course.

40:34.775 --> 40:37.510
And I worked like hell to get
those people to trust me again,

40:37.511 --> 40:39.378
but the problem was
I didn't trust them.

40:39.379 --> 40:41.214
The day I quit was the day I realized

40:41.215 --> 40:43.615
I didn't want to have
to throw furniture anymore.

40:46.319 --> 40:48.020
But then you tracked me
down at a pita place

40:48.021 --> 40:49.522
to talk about permafrost...

40:49.523 --> 40:51.324
Yeah, sorry about ambushing your meal.

40:51.325 --> 40:52.492
No, no, no, I loved it.

40:52.493 --> 40:53.860
You knew you didn't have it yet

40:53.861 --> 40:56.262
and you weren't gonna
stop until you did.

40:56.263 --> 40:58.263
Do you know how rare that is?

40:59.332 --> 41:02.802
Look, all I wanted to say was

41:02.803 --> 41:05.071
I know you're looking
for a policy advisor

41:05.072 --> 41:06.606
and I want to throw my hat
in the ring.

41:06.607 --> 41:11.844
I am open-minded but decisive.

41:11.845 --> 41:15.648
I will walk through fire
to make things happen for you

41:15.649 --> 41:19.618
and I promise my furniture-
throwing days are over.

41:21.354 --> 41:25.223
You had me at permafrost.

41:27.860 --> 41:33.399
She actually threw a
table at a senator.

41:33.400 --> 41:38.637
I mean, how often is the real
story even worse than the rumor?

41:40.139 --> 41:43.276
You think I'm crazy for hiring her.

41:43.277 --> 41:44.977
What?

41:44.978 --> 41:46.846
Sorry.

41:46.847 --> 41:49.115
Look, I think I need to talk.

41:49.116 --> 41:51.083
It's about the leak

41:51.084 --> 41:53.618
that led to Nafisa being taken.

41:55.321 --> 41:57.190
Who was it?

41:57.191 --> 41:58.391
I still don't know.

41:58.392 --> 42:00.159
There's a task force
looking at the agents

42:00.160 --> 42:02.394
being blown in multiple departments.

42:04.096 --> 42:06.465
Okay. So, they're looking into it.

42:06.466 --> 42:08.668
- That's good.
- But the blown ops,

42:08.669 --> 42:11.971
in order to have access
to that level of Intel,

42:11.972 --> 42:13.873
you'd have to be
on the president's cabinet.

42:13.874 --> 42:15.173
Which is crazy.

42:16.876 --> 42:19.144
I know.

42:22.014 --> 42:24.515
That leaves only eight
other people it could be.

42:24.516 --> 42:25.598
Henry.

42:25.599 --> 42:28.254
Someone in the Congressional
Gang of Eight

42:28.255 --> 42:30.823
could be selling out our country.

42:30.824 --> 42:34.126
I don't know who. I don't know why.

42:34.127 --> 42:38.263
And I hope to hell I'm wrong,
but what if I'm not?

